DTSTAMP:20260428T232841Z
UID:7d4h2fius2k6skraplnsauvu0g@google.com
CREATED:20260224T173211Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>The Office of Religious Affairs is delighted to inform the D
 AT community that the first day of Ramadan and the obligation of fasting wi
 ll be either Wed\, February 18 or Thurs\, February 19\, pending verified gl
 obal moon sighting.</p><p></p><p>In making this determination\, God willing
 \, DAT will be aligned with other major masajid in our area that follow glo
 bal sighting\, including DUS\, PGMA\, ICCL\, and ISB\, and national organiz
 ations\, in order to maintain unity within our local Muslim community.</p><
 p>Accordingly\, the first night of Taraweeh will be either Tuesday night\, 
 February 17 or Wednesday night\, February 18\, depending on the confirmed s
 ighting..An official confirmation will be shared as soon as the moon sighti
 ng has been verified.</p><p>May Allah allow us to reach Ramadan in good hea
 lth and accept from us our fasting\, prayers\, and good deeds.</p><p></p><p
 >Shaykh Aamir </p><p>Director of Religious Affairs</p><p>Dar Al Taqwa\, Mar
 yland </p><p><a href="www.taqwa.net">www.taqwa.net</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T173211Z
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY: (Tentative) Start of Fasting
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
